  "text": "The view of mothers as \"little more than architects of the perfect child\" has important implications for the self-concept of mothers (7). Self-concept is defined as the combination of one's perceptions and values with regard to him/herself, which is constructed through social interactions. Recent theories on the development of self-concept tend to focus on an individual's view of self in comparison to others [CITATION_1] .",
